file=Engineering/dana/custom/migration-discipline/assets/migration-script-template.md · ms—:Migration Script — [name] — [store] — [date]=> Rail 3 artifact. dana authors; the OPERATOR runs. Reversible (tested down-script) or explicit operator sign-off + recovery plan. Sequenced expand→migrate→contract.\n · es(:Effect summary (plain language — the operator approves THIS)=[What it does, in human terms. Tables/collections/edges affected. Estimated rows. What it explicitly does NOT touch. Reversible? yes/no.]\n · u:Up-script=```\n[the forward migration — in the store's language: SQL / HelixQL / migration DSL]\n```\n · d(:Down-script (reversible)=```\n[the rollback — restores the prior schema/state]\n```\n- Down tested on scratch/restored copy: [ ✓ evidence ref ] — untested = NOT DONE\n- If irreversible: operator sign-off ref [___] + recovery plan [___] + risk entry [___]\n · s:Sequencing=- Phase: [expand / migrate / contract]\n- This step independently rollback-able: [ ✓ / explanation ]\n · e(3:Execution (Rail 3)=- Authored by: dana\n- **TO BE RUN BY: OPERATOR** (dana does not execute — no environment, no urgency exception)\n- Operator approved: [ ___ ] \· Operator ran: [ date ___ ]\n · tb=\| expected (from summary) \| actual \| match \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| \| \| ✓/✗ → incident if ✗ \| · pv:Post-run verification=→ ops deploy record: [ref] \· quinn gate evidence: [ref]\n